DURBAN - THE police in KwaZulu-Natal have appealed for members of the public to come forward to assist with information regarding a rape case they are investigating. They released an identikit which they believe can assist in finding the man. The Durban Central Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit said it was looking for information regarding a 24-year-old man who allegedly raped a mentally disturbed woman at her place of residence in Queen Street, Durban. The incident happened on June 24 at about 4.30pm. “It is alleged that on 24 June 2018 at 16:30, a victim, 24, went to the ladies room at her place of residence in Queen Street, Durban, when she was accosted by an unknown male who forcefully raped her. “The victim in this case is mentally disturbed and she was instructed not to tell anyone about the rape,” said police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele. “Police believe that the man in the attached identikit can assist in solving the case. Anyone with the information on the male in the attached identikit is urged to contact the police,” she said. Detective Sergeant Buhle Masondo on 031 325 4142/ 0718759834 or Crime Stop number on 08600 10111.